# GroupStage environment — copy to `.env.local` for local dev.
#
# These keys are read ONLY by the Hono serverless proxy (api/), never by the
# browser bundle. The client always calls our own /api/* routes. If a key is
# missing, the proxy returns a clear 503 and the app falls back to bundled
# mock/historical data — nothing in the UI hard-fails.

# API-Football (api-sports.io) — PRIMARY live source. Its free tier (100
# requests/day) DOES include the World Cup, so this is what powers live scores.
# Register free at https://www.api-football.com/ and paste the key here.
# World Cup is league 1; the 2026 edition is season 2026 (overridable in the proxy).
API_FOOTBALL_KEY=

# football-data.org free tier — SECONDARY fallback (its free tier does NOT
# include the World Cup, so it rarely returns WC fixtures; kept for other comps).
# Get one free at https://www.football-data.org/client/register
FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY=

# The Odds API free tier — bookmaker consensus odds (de-vigged client-side).
# Get one free at https://the-odds-api.com/
ODDS_API_KEY=

# Polymarket Gamma API needs no key (public), so it is not listed here.
